ikely does not need changes if published keys keep the current\nshape. It should continue to consume only materialized public metadata from\n`refs/meta/main`.\n\nIf downstream behavior does need to change, the downstream scope should be\nlimited to `[REDACTED:path]`.\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- Where should the local-to-published key move live: upstream in `git-meta-lib`\n  as a generic primitive, or locally in `but-agentlog` as agentlog-specific\n  behavior?\n","tool_name":"exec_command","tool_kind":"exec","tool_input":null,"exit_code":0,"outcome":"succeeded","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-31T16:31:30.917Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}